text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia imparilis is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Great Southern region of Western Australia.The erect pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 0.5 metres (0.7 to 1.6 ft) and produces cream-yellow flowers in October.
